{"id_":"5334602a-49d2-479b-915f-025ef31d0100","metadata":{"url":"https://api-docs.jetdelivery.com/"},"excludedEmbedMetadataKeys":[],"excludedLlmMetadataKeys":[],"relationships":{},"text":"Jet Delivery - API v1           BodyHeaders (7)BodyHeaders (7)BodyHeaders (7)  Public Documentation SettingsENVIRONMENTjetdelivery.com - ProductionLAYOUTDouble ColumnLANGUAGEcURL - cURLJet Delivery - API v1Introduction GETTrack shipmentsGETRates and transit timesPOSTSchedule shipmentsPOSTCancel shipmentsPOSTFile UploadGETFile Upload | DeleteGETGet documentsJet Delivery - API v1This is a Postman collection for the Jet Delivery API endpoints. The information provided here aims to explain how you can tie our core shipping, tracking, and rating services directly into your web applications and/or ERP systems.
This will give your business the ability to offer an integrated same-day shipping option to any destination within the United States. Please see the following documentation for more details: https://www.jetdelivery.com/developer/. In case you have an API related question, you can call us at 800-203-1633.
Installation
Go to the collection then just click Run in Postman.
Environment
This collection includes a pre-configured environment setting. You will be needing to set up below variables in order to run each request:



Name
Description




key
Your Api key



The API key you use to authenticate the request determines whether the request is live mode or test mode.
GETTrack shipmentshttps://www.jetdelivery.com/api/v1/utilities/track/?id=2345678&ref=&key=key_test_2rWvqrGtfgb51yuiR428ektYou can use our tracking endpoint to get the real-time status of your shipment. The results include the GPS location of the driver (when available), reference, signature, event history, and more.
No api-key is required to use this endpoint. In it's simplest form, an API call may look like: https://www.jetdelivery.com/api/v1/utilities/track/?idx=2345678
For security reasons, unless you provide an api-key we will display only the weighted center of each zip-code rather than the exact origin and destination locations.
PARAMSid2345678Required. This can be the 6-8 digit tracking number assigned to your shipment at the time of booking, or it can be the unique billing reference provided to us. Up to 23 characters.
refOptional. Sending "link-ref" attempts to match the "id" to a billing reference in our system rather than our tracking number.
keykey_test_2rWvqrGtfgb51yuiR428ektOptional. This is your unique API key, linked to a specific Jet Delivery account.

}Cache-ControlprivateContent-Typeapplication/json; charset=utf-8ServerjwsX-AspNet-Version4.0.30319X-Powered-ByASP.NETDateThu, 29 Oct 2020 22:00:38 GMTContent-Length1345GETRates and transit timeshttps://www.jetdelivery.com/api/v1/utilities/quote/?origin=90021&destination=91750&pieces=1&weight=1&pickup_req_date=&pickup_req_time=&deliver_req_date=&deliver_req_time=&key=key_test_2rWvqrGtfgb51yuiR428ektYou can use our quote endpoint to check rates and estimate transit times. Depending on the zip-codes you enter, different services may or may not be available. 
No api-key is required to use this endpoint. However, if you don't send an api-key in your request, you will not get any special pricing that applies to your specific account. 
In it's simplest form, an API call may look like: https://www.jetdelivery.com/api/v1/utilities/quote/?origin=90021&destination=91750
PARAMSorigin90021Required. This should be the 5-digit zip code the shipment is originating from.
destination91750Required. This should be the 5-digit zip code the shipment is delivering to.
pieces1Optional. Total number of pieces. 
weight1Optional. Total weight of shipment.
pickup_req_dateOptional. Date shipment will be ready for pickup. Use  MM/DD/YYYY format. If left blank, the date will default to the current day. Note Weekends and holidays may have an impact on the pricing returned.
pickup_req_timeOptional. Time shipment will be ready for pickup. Use  24-hour format HH:MM. If left blank the time will default to the current time. 
deliver_req_dateOptional. Date shipment must be delivered on. Use MM/DD/YYYY format. If left blank, the date will default to ASAP.
deliver_req_timeOptional. Time shipment should be delivered by. Use  24-hour format HH:MM. If left blank the time will default to ASAP. 
keykey_test_2rWvqrGtfgb51yuiR428ektOptional. This is your unique API key, linked to a specific Jet Delivery account.

Please see the following documentation for more details: https://www.jetdelivery.com/developer/. In case you have an API related question, you can call us at 800-203-1633.
Installation
Go to the collection then just click Run in Postman.
Environment
This collection includes a pre-configured environment setting. You will be needing to set up below variables in order to run each request:

key
Your Api keyThe API key you use to authenticate the request determines whether the request is live mode or test mode.GETTrack shipmentshttps://www.jetdelivery.com/api/v1/utilities/track/?id=2345678&ref=&key=key_test_2rWvqrGtfgb51yuiR428ektYou can use our tracking endpoint to get the real-time status of your shipment.The results include the GPS location of the driver (when available), reference, signature, event history, and more.No api-key is required to use this endpoint.In it's simplest form, an API call may look like: https://www.jetdelivery.com/api/v1/utilities/track/?idx=2345678
For security reasons, unless you provide an api-key we will display only the weighted center of each zip-code rather than the exact origin and destination locations.PARAMSid2345678Required.This can be the 6-8 digit tracking number assigned to your shipment at the time of booking, or it can be the unique billing reference provided to us.Up to 23 characters.refOptional.Sending "link-ref" attempts to match the "id" to a billing reference in our system rather than our tracking number.keykey_test_2rWvqrGtfgb51yuiR428ektOptional.This is your unique API key, linked to a specific Jet Delivery account.Example RequestTrack shipmentsView Morecurlcurl --location 'https://www.jetdelivery.com/api/v1/utilities/track/?id=2345678&ref=&key=key_test_2rWvqrGtfgb51yuiR428ekt'200 OKExample ResponseBodyHeaders (7)View Morejson{
